Program: The Reith Lectures
Title: Patterns of Identity
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00h4n5x
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 5 Dec 1979
Professor of Political Science at the University of Michigan, Ali Mazrui, explores Africa's lack of cohesion in his fifth Reith lecture from his series entitled 'The African Condition'. In this lecture entitled 'Patterns of Identity', Professor Ali Mazrui argues that an understanding of the size and fragmentation of Africa is essential in diagnosing the nature of its aches and pains. Show less